<whdroplet name="drDemoSetupcoderage">
<ol>
<li> Firebird 2.5 </li>
<li> Database created by parsing public Embarcadero web pages for 2009-2011, and inserting relevant data via TIB_DSQL; 3 tables plus Rubicon keyword index.
<ul>
<li> <a target="_blank" href="http://edn.embarcadero.com/article/39727">Code Rage 4, October 2009</a></li>
<li> <a target="_blank" href="http://www.embarcadero.com/coderage5/sessions">Code Rage 5, October 2010</a></li>
<li> <a target="_blank" href="http://www.embarcadero.com/coderage/sessions">Code Rage 6, October 2011</a></li>

</ul>
 </li>
<li> Firebird database name, username and password stored in XML file pointed to by ZaphodsMap configuration. Reference
<a target="_blank" href="http://webhub.com/dynhelp:alias::zmlookupfirebirdcredentials">ZMLookup_Firebird_Credentials</a> and use project abbreviation of CodeRageScheduleLOCAL. </li>
<li> Compilation of the source code requires Delphi, Rubicon v4, Interbase Objects v5 plus WebHub (~version~).  A few in-house units are used in this particular demo; they are available upon request for any WebHub or Rubicon customers.</li>
</ol>

